Package: prg
Title: Creates the Precision-Recall-Gain curve and calculates the area under the curve
Version: 0.5.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Meelis", "Kull", email = "meelis.kull@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre")),
    person("Peter", "Flach", email = "peter.flach@bristol.ac.uk", role = c("aut")))
Description: Precision-Recall-Gain (PRG) curves are enhancements of the Precision-Recall (PR) curves. 
    The benefits of PRG-curves over PR-curves are: 
    (1) universal baselines over non-universal;
    (2) linear interpolation over non-linear;
    (3) linear F-isometrics over non-linear;
    (4) convex Pareto front over non-convex;
    (5) area-under-PRG-curve relates to expected F-gain, area-under-PR-curve does not relate to expected F-measure.
Depends: 
    R (>= 3.1.0)
Imports:
    ggplot2 (>= 1.0.0),
    grid
License: MIT + file LICENSE
LazyData: true

